# 🎯 Day 7 - Hangman Game

This is a Python implementation of the classic Hangman game, developed as part of the **100 Days of Code** challenge.

The player guesses letters to uncover a hidden word before running out of lives. The game includes ASCII art to visually represent the hangman’s progress.

## 🚀 Features

- Word selection from a predefined list
- Visual representation with ASCII art
- User input handling and feedback
- Tracks incorrect guesses and lives remaining

## 🛠️ Built With

- Python 3
- `random` module

## 🧠 What I Practiced

- Loops and conditional logic
- Lists and string manipulation
- Displaying ASCII graphics
- Game state management

---

Part of the [100 Days of Code](https://github.com/Synel96/100-Days-Of-Code) journey.
